No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[173,1296,765,794]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="237.[171,1378,291,1070]" box="[173,1296,765,794]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,307,765,794]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842">Breeding.</emphasis>
Juvenile SulaArchipelago Rats were collected in September—October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[171,1252,804,833]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="237.[171,1378,291,1070]" box="[171,1252,804,833]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,406,804,833]" pageId="237" pageNumber="842">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Sula Archipelago Ratis nocturnal and likely terrestrial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
